T|Hour|8|The window btw "pricing approved" and "first us lands" is the instrumentation window — the period when an tracking must be built into the pd. If that window is missed, ka spends the first 90 days post-launch retrofitting measurement instead of producing intelligence. Yesterday's brief recommended writing the event tracking spec now; that recommendation stands and gains urgency w/ each day the pd bd proceeds w/o an scaffolding.
T|Hour|9|
T|Hour|10|Action: Write the hb event tracking specification today — before the pd bd outpaces it. Deliverable:
T|Hour|11|Define every us action that gets instrumented: signup, trial start, first workspace created, first transaction logged, invite sent, upgrade to paid, churn event.
T|Hour|12|Specify properties per event (userid, ventureid, timestamp, session_id, feature flags active).
T|Hour|13|Define cohort segments: trial-started-this-week, active-4-of-4-weeks, churned-after-trial, upgraded-within-14-days.
T|Hour|14|Pre-configure alert thresholds from ag.md: M1 retention < 65% → onboarding broken (flag nt + dv); LTV:CAC < 2:1 → pause acquisition spend (flag fx + mc).
T|Hour|15|Deliver as a markdown spec to /doc/vt/hb/ANALYTICS_SPEC.md and rt to dv/rj via dn's sprint planning.
T|Hour|16|
T|Hour|17|Confidence: hi — this is standard pre-launch SaaS an practice and carries negligible risk. The risk is entirely in omission: if the spec isn't written before the pd bd completes, the cost of retrofitting an is 3-5x the cost of building it in from the start (software engineering base rate).
