T|Cros|5|The common thread: ka's posture needs to shift from consumer of data to owner of the data pipeline. The ag.md routing table assigns ka an ownership, but ka cannot execute on that ownership w/o (a) db access for nz and (b) instrumentation authority for hb. dn (co) shd add "verify an pipeline live" to the Monday checklist, and Stark shd treat the absence of an data w/ the same urgency as a bd fl — bc a cg launched blind and a cg launched w/ data differ by 30-40% in first-month ROAS.
